    "client_msg_id": "7733034f-6e7b-4969-b02d-f9913eba4c31",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "I think this is a useful categorisation of applications. There's arguably some overlap between categories, e.g. Wikipedia can be used in an exploratory manner. I also noticed you've mixed _activities_ and _artifacts_ together, e.g. \"data analysis\" and \"cars\". I wonder if it's possible to tweak things to be more consistent.\n\nNow that we've got this diagram, it would be interesting to come up with a second one that breaks systems into abstractions, e.g. \"interfaces\", \"messages\", \"state\", \"behaviour\".  I'm not sure if there's an unbiased way to do this though, it probably results in making too many assumptions about how a system \"should\" be viewed.",
